          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-821873?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCredit">照片：《华尔街日报》</p></figcaption></figure></div></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 25 Jul 2023 04:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/pepper-and-salt-f32161db</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/pepper-and-salt-f32161db<category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>社论</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>仅标题内容</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>社论</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>仅标题内容</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Israel’s Supreme Court Panic Attack]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>妥协是摆脱困境的出路，不需要乔·拜登的帮助。 <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB11786258192805913745104590108263487507380"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB11786258192805913745104590108263487507380"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/editorial-board" itemprop="url" rel="author">编委会</a></span>撰文</div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 24 日下午 6:38 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/israel-judicial-reform-benjamin-netanyahu-benny-gantz-yair-lapid-e306889b"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-822953?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> 7月22日，数千名反政府抗议者在进入耶路撒冷的抗议游行中举着以色列国旗，集会反对以色列政府的司法改革计划。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：abir sultan/Shutterstock</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>以色列的民主正处于危险之中，其抵御外国威胁的能力正在消亡，而且更糟糕的情况还在后面。这就是周一过度紧张的媒体和政治叙事，因为犹太国家通过了一项适度的司法改革，这项改革可能不会像双方声称的那样产生太大影响。</p><div class="media-object scope-web,mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p>新法律禁止以色列最高法院进行合理性测试，该测试允许法院根据对该词的解释推翻政府行为。新法律刚刚开始扭转 20 世纪 80 年代和 90 年代的“司法革命”，以色列法院在这场革命中声称拥有不同寻常的新权力。新法律的目的是通过一些东西，任何东西，向保守派选民表明政府还没有完全被反对派抗议所推翻。</p><p>在以色列，“合理性”最初是在地方层面作为普通法引入的，但后来成为一种通用工具，使政府任命、军事决策和具有国家意义的政策无效。这给了法院很大的自由裁量权，但结果往往是武断的。例如，法院认为看守政府通过任命中层官员来约束未来政府是不合理的。但它发现另一个看守政府向巴勒斯坦人提供最终地位和平协议是合理的。</p><p>周一投票前不久，反对派领导人本尼·甘茨和亚伊尔·拉皮德提出接受“合理性”改革，以换取推迟内塔尼亚胡政府首次提出的更大规模改革。他们明白，这种变化本身并不是危险，但要阻止最初的、更广泛的改革所引发的抗议运动已经太晚了。</p><p>抗议者封锁高速公路、宣布罢工并逃避预备役义务，而大学和企业则放走了学生和工人。抵制储备税一直是对以色列政府的有效施压策略。但在军事准备的情况下玩弄政治是以色列无法承受的放纵，而指望军方高层进行政治干预并不是“拯救民主”的方法。</p><p>周一晚上，总理本杰明·内塔尼亚胡呼吁就改革的其余部分达成妥协，这是有道理的，会谈将持续到 11 月。但他能否阻止他的联盟伙伴要求走得更远呢？在强烈的反对声中，这很可能会失败。</p><p>妥协需要时间，而时间可能会证明新的“合理性”法律几乎没有改变。法官们并没有失去任命新法官的实质性权力。法院仍然可以审理几乎任何案件，即使是在没有原告受到直接伤害的严格政治问题上。法院保留了 20 世纪 90 年代夺取的推翻立法的权力，并且仍然可以以各种理由阻止行政行为，但不合理的理由除外，而不合理的理由有很多替代方案。换句话说，以色列的司法机构并没有真正进行改革，民主也没有消亡。</p><p>拜登总统对这场以色列内部辩论的持续评论是不体面的，看起来旨在推翻总理本杰明·内塔尼亚胡的政府。两国应该共同努力将《亚伯拉罕协议》扩展到沙特阿拉伯并阻止伊朗的核计划。以色列的司法辩论远远落后于中东的紧迫问题。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=79574680-0106-44EF-A6E4-6BC8AF5022CB&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fisrael-judicial-reform-benjamin-netanyahu-benny-gantz-yair-lapid-e306889b&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">尽管努力压制他的声音，2024 年民主党总统候选人小罗伯特·F·肯尼迪 (Robert F. Kennedy Jr.) 在联邦政府审查制度听证会上仍捍卫言论自由和第一修正案。图片：彭博新闻/盖蒂图片社 综合：马克·凯利<span class="imageCredit">华尔街日报互动版</span></p></div></div></section></div></main></div>]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 24 Jul 2023 22:38:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/israel-judicial-reform-b​​enjamin-netanyahu-benny-gantz-yair-lapid-e306889b</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/israel-judicial-reform-b​​enjamin-netanyahu-benny-gantz-yair-lapid-e306889b<author><![CDATA[The Editorial Board]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>以色列最高法院</category><category>本杰明·内塔尼亚胡</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[BlackRock’s False Voting ‘Choice’]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>资产管理公司表示，他们正在为投资者提供新的代理投票选择。但权力仍然掌握在代理顾问双寡头格拉斯·刘易斯（Glass Lewis）和国际空间站（ISS）手中。 <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB10950590414055573352804590102330203026598"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB10950590414055573352804590102330203026598"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/editorial-board" itemprop="url" rel="author">编委会</a></span>撰文</div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 24 日下午 6:38 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/blackrocks-false-voting-choice-proxy-esg-ballots-iss-glass-lewis-66652357"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-822301?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">贝莱德总部位于纽约。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：迈克尔·内格尔/彭博新闻</p></figcaption></figure></div><p><a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/BLK" class="company-name">贝莱德</a>因据称使散户投资者的代理投票民主化而赢得了媒体的赞誉。要是。相反，这家资产管理公司正试图平息对其环境、社会和治理（ESG）方法的批评，同时授权代理咨询双寡头推动同样的进步议程。</p><div class="media-object scope-web,mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p>与其他资产管理公司一样，贝莱德传统上为其指数基金的散户投资者进行代理投票。然而，它最近受到了保守派的批评，因为它利用 9.4 万亿美元的资产来推动上市公司采用 ESG 目标，包括二氧化碳排放和其他“可持续性”披露。</p><p>去年秋天，十九个共和党州总检察长致信贝莱德首席执行官拉里·芬克，警告其作为净零资产管理公司计划的一部分与其他金融机构的协调存在反垄断问题。股份公司还指出，贝莱德惩罚不遵守其气候指令的公司董事会董事的政策可能违反其对投资者的信托义务。</p><p>贝莱德在某种程度上得到了这一信息。上周，该公司宣布，从明年开始，其最受欢迎的交易所交易基金的超过 300 万散户投资者将能够从一系列代理投票政策选项中进行选择。致共和党总检察长的信息：如果贝莱德为散户投资者提供投票选择，就不存在反垄断或信托违规行为。</p><p>没那么快。贝莱德几乎所有预先选定的投票政策都是由 Glass Lewis 和机构股东服务公司 (ISS) 的代理咨询双寡头制定的，这两家公司都支持 ESG 投资。其中包括格拉斯刘易斯的气候政策和国际空间站的社会责任投资政策。即使是表面上不注重 ESG 的选项，例如 ISS 的天主教信仰政策，也支持减排、董事会多元化配额和种族平等审计等措施。</p><p> “贝莱德致力于让每个投资者都可以选择参与股东投票过程，”该公司全球投资管理主管表示。好吧，但他们仍然无法真正选择如何投票。贝莱德的“投票选择”举措让人想起亨利·福特的名言：顾客可以将汽车漆成任何颜色，只要它是黑色的。</p><p> ISS 的贝莱德选项确实广泛支持公司董事会的建议，而这些建议往往对 ESG 决议不太友好。但大多数投资者并不在所有问题上都支持公司董事会。根据这项政策，当公司业绩不佳时，投资者不能单独反对首席执行官的薪酬。</p><p>贝莱德似乎更关心获得政治和法律保护，而不是为投资者提供真正的投票选择。它并不孤单。先锋集团和<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/STT" class="company-name">道富银行</a>今年早些时候推出了类似的举措。先锋集团的四个选择包括其自己的建议、与公司董事会一致的政策、Glass Lewis ESG 政策和弃权。</p><p>道富银行的七种投票选项均由 ISS 准备，大部分都符合 ESG，其中包括一种基于 AFL-CIO 指南的投票选项。另一项“寻求促进对公认的全球管理机构的支持，促进可持续商业实践，倡导环境管理、公平劳动实践、非歧视和保护人权。”</p><p>资产管理公司和代理咨询公司之间的这种协调可能会加剧共和党股份公司提出的反垄断担忧。贝莱德及其同行正试图通过将投票建议委托给代理顾问来逃避为投资者的最佳财务利益行事的信托责任，代理顾问充当养老基金的 ESG 力量乘数。</p><p>抱歉，贝莱德，投资者应该得到比这些更好的选择。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=FDCCF5A6-4DE9-4327-AA4A-056B0B052CB1&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fblackrocks-false-voting-choice-proxy-esg-ballots-iss-glass-lewis-66652357&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">杂志社论报道：国税局举报人称司法部干预了他们对亨特·拜登的调查。图片：Zuma Press/AFP/Getty Images 合成：Mark Kelly<span class="imageCredit">华尔街日报互动版</span></p></div></div></section></div></main></div>]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 24 Jul 2023 22:38:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/blackrocks-false-voting-choice-proxy-esg-ballots-iss-glass-lewis-66652357</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/blackrocks-false-voting-choice-proxy-esg-ballots-iss-glass-lewis-66652357<author><![CDATA[The Editorial Board]]></author><category>代理投票</category><category>养老基金</category><category>资产管理人</category><category>国家股份公司</category><category>投票倡议</category><category>环境、社会及治理</category><category>金融投资服务</category><category>投资组合/基金/资产管理</category><category>金融服务</category><category>投资/证券</category><category>法规/政府政策</category><category>反竞争问题</category><category>管理</category><category>股东积极性</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>公司治理</category><category>企业社会责任</category><category>企业环境责任</category><category>环境/社会/治理</category><category>代理权之争</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>气候变化</category><category>自然环境</category><category>全球/世界问题</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>规定</category><category>政府政策</category><category>反竞争问题</category><category>管理</category><category>股东积极主义</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>公司治理</category><category>企业社会责任</category><category>企业环境责任</category><category>环境的</category><category>社会的</category><category>治理</category><category>代理人之争</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>气候变化</category><category>自然环境</category><category>全球的</category><category>世界问题</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>金融投资服务</category><category>文件夹</category><category>基金</category><category>资产管理</category><category>金融服务</category><category>投资</category><category>证券</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[America’s Choice: Immigration or Bust]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>到 2040 年，美国的劳动年龄人口可能会减少 600 万。 <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB11277182998813654381604590102422492038514"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB11277182998813654381604590102422492038514"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/editorial-board" itemprop="url" rel="author">编委会</a></span>撰文</div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 24 日下午 6:36 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/americas-choice-immigration-or-bust-aging-population-work-unemployment-border-738a56bb"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-822300?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCredit">照片：Rogelio V. Solis/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>美国存在人员问题。出生率多年来一直在下降，这将转化为劳动力的萎缩。根据本周发布的一项研究，到 2040 年，美国的劳动年龄人口可能比 2022 年减少 600 万以上。应对国内趋势的唯一方法是吸引海外工人。</p><div class="media-object scope-web,mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p> “在没有更多移民的情况下，美国劳动年龄人口已经达到顶峰，”马德琳·扎沃德尼在美国政策国家基金会即将发表的一篇论文中写道。 “新的国际移民是未来二十年剩余时间内美国劳动年龄人口增长的唯一潜在来源。”扎沃德尼女士是北佛罗里达大学的经济学教授，她的分析基于人口普查局和劳工统计局的数据。</p><p>当一些美国人将外国工人视为廉价竞争者时，她提供了增长和活力的处方。她特别指出，尽管从 2021 年 1 月到 2023 年 5 月，外国出生的工人占美国就业增长的近一半，但“在此期间，美国出生的壮年工人的就业人数也猛增。”</p><p>她补充说，失业率一直处于历史低位，如果工作年龄人口减少，找到优秀工人的难度将会增加。</p><p>国内趋势线并不好，有两大原因。出生率下降就是其中之一。另一个原因是婴儿潮一代的寿命更长，并且随着年龄的增长而退出劳动力市场。任何认为人口减少是令人愉快的人都应该在日本和意大利呆上一段时间。正如这些国家所发现的那样，衰退意味着生产商品和服务的人数减少，创新也减少。就连中国共产党人现在也承认，由于他们推行独生子女政策，正如米尔顿·弗里德曼所预测的那样，他们现在面临着巨大的劳动力短缺，这将挑战经济增长。</p><p>扎沃德尼女士表示，到目前为止，美国已经能够通过移民进行补偿，移民是“2021 年和 2022 年美国劳动年龄人口增长的唯一来源”。但这并不能保证。她提出，受到出生率下降和老龄化社会双重打击的国家之间的未来竞争。加拿大最近推出了一项新的工作许可证，以吸引持有高技能 H-1B 签证的外国人到美国。两天内就达到了 10,000 名申请人的目标。</p><p>在唐纳德·特朗普谈论隔离墙和<a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/joe-biden">乔·拜登</a>在南部边境制造混乱的背景下，很难想象国会会在 2025 年之前提出任何解决方案。但扎沃德尼女士指出，劳动力趋势如果不得到解决，将会产生破坏性后果。需要有人证明接纳外国工人对美国人有好处。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=5142C94E-13A6-499A-B6D4-6A6C8A9266FE&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Famericas-choice-immigration-or-bust-aging-population-work-unemployment-border-738a56bb&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">仙境：美国经常被描述为“移民国家”，但随着拜登的开放河流或特朗普的另一堵墙，美国卓越地位的时钟可能会停止，因为非法移民玷污了获得公民身份的合法途径。图片：法新社/盖蒂图片社/祖玛出版社 综合：马克·凯利<span class="imageCredit">华尔街日报互动版</span></p></div></div></section></div></main></div>]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 24 Jul 2023 22:36:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/americas-choice-immigration-or-bust-aging-population-work-unemployment-border-738a56bb</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/americas-choice-immigration-or-bust-aging-population-work-unemployment-border-738a56bb<author><![CDATA[The Editorial Board]]></author><category>移民</category><category>出生率</category><category>南部边境</category><category>失业</category><category>劳动年龄人口</category><category>独生子女政策</category><category>婴儿潮一代</category><category>人口老龄化</category><category>生育能力</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>社会/社区</category><category>人口统计</category><category>人类迁徙</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>社会</category><category>社区</category><category>人口统计</category><category>人类迁徙</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[A Northeast Progressive Cage Match]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>特伦顿援引 NEPA 环境法来停止纽约的拥堵交通税。 <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB11754030163052123715304590108203829281946"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB11754030163052123715304590108203829281946"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/editorial-board" itemprop="url" rel="author">编委会</a></span>撰文</div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 24 日下午 6:35 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/new-jersey-new-york-lawsuit-congestion-pricing-tolls-nepa-785fc45"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-823005?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">新泽西州伊丽莎白戈索尔斯大桥东行跨度</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：凯西·威伦斯/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>新泽西州周五就拜登政府批准纽约拥堵收费计划起诉拜登政府，这一讽刺让人很难不微笑。看看一个进步的州如何利用联邦环境法来阻止贪婪的进步邻国征税。</p><div class="media-object scope-web,mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p> 2019 年，纽约颁布了一项法律，授权对进入曼哈顿中央商务区的司机收取通行费。由于该计划不包括该市的西区高速公路和罗斯福大道，因此该税将主要针对居住在曼哈顿上东区和西区的花园州居民和司机。</p><p> 1991 年的一项法律要求联邦公路管理局 (FHWA) 批准接受联邦资助的州和地方高速公路的通行费。特伦顿表示，联邦公路管理局未能按照《国家环境政策法案》(NEPA) 的要求，对拥堵税的潜在影响进行彻底的环境分析。</p><p>美国联邦公路局确定纽约的收费计划不会对环境产生重大影响，但新泽西州声称它将改变交通流量和污染物。据称，这将给新泽西州的低收入社区带来负担，尽管曼哈顿居民据称因在城市核心行驶的汽车减少而受益于更清洁的空气。</p><p>诉讼称：“连接新泽西州和纽约史坦顿岛的联合县戈索尔斯大桥和外桥交叉路口可能会出现避开曼哈顿（中央商务区）的车辆流量增加。”并补充说，“在卑尔根县，各类污染物都会增加。”</p><p>新泽西州认为，NEPA 要求各机构考虑行动的“间接影响”，拜登总统的行政命令要求他们“将实现环境正义作为其使命的一部分”。你不得不嘲笑新泽西州援引拜登总统的命令，这些命令旨在阻止化石燃料项目，以便花园州可以阻止税收掠夺。</p><p>新泽西州真正想要的是分享税收收益。州诉讼称，纽约市大都会交通管理局已同意将收入分配给长岛铁路和大都会北方铁路，但不会分配给新泽西州的交通机构。 MTA 还为布朗克斯区的“环境缓解”项目提供了 1.3 亿美元的资金。</p><p>新泽西州州长菲尔·墨菲 (Phil Murphy) 希望 MTA 也为该州的“缓解措施”提供资金。游击队经常为了自己的目的而滥用 NEPA，这是另一个恰当的例子。两个州都能输掉这场官司吗？ </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=E8C29630-C6D9-4EC5-819B-1922608C0EAF&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fnew-jersey-new-york-lawsuit-congestion-pricing-tolls-nepa-785fc45&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">杂志社论报道：现在判断“无标签”是否有助于特朗普赢得 2024 年大选还为时过早。图片：美联社/法新社/盖蒂图片社 综合：马克·凯利<span class="imageCredit">华尔街日报互动版</span></p></div></div></section></div></main></div>]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 24 Jul 2023 22:35:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/new-jersey-new-york-lawsuit-congestion-pricing-tolls-nepa-785fc45</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/new-jersey-new-york-lawsuit-congestion-pricing-tolls-nepa-785fc45<author><![CDATA[The Editorial Board]]></author><category>政府财政</category><category>政府预算/税收</category><category>地方政府预算/税收</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>自然环境</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>国家环境保护局</category><category>联邦公路管理局 (FHWA)</category><category>政府财政</category><category>政府预算</category><category>税收</category><category>地方政府预算</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>自然环境</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[New York Times Reports on Nasty Progressives]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>一位民主党人在学生贷款问题上与她的政党作对。 <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB11490979256760064080404590108312269658590"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB11490979256760064080404590108312269658590"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="columnist_mini"> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/james-freeman"><img width="45" height="45" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/B3-BG857_freema_AM_20180731103058.jpg" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></a></div><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/james-freeman" itemprop="url" rel="author">詹姆斯·弗里曼</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 24 日下午 6:18 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/new-york-times-reports-on-nasty-progressives-b9a19abd"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-822910?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">众议员玛丽·格鲁森坎普·佩雷斯（华盛顿州民主党人）将于四月份抵达美国国会大厦进行一系列投票。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：汤姆·威廉姆斯/祖玛出版社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>偏离总统关于学生贷款救助的议程似乎是激怒进步左翼的好方法。但第一任众议员玛丽·格鲁森坎普·佩雷斯（华盛顿州民主党人）可能没有意识到反对她政策的人会采取何种形式。</p><p>安妮·卡尼 (Annie Karni) <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2023/07/22/us/politics/marie-gluesenkamp-perez-democrats-student-loans.html" target="_blank" class="icon none">为《纽约时报》报道：</a></p><blockquote> Dean&#39;s Car Care 是俄勒冈州波特兰市的一家汽车修理店，过去因其可靠、友好的服务经常获得五颗星，并在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/YELP" class="company-name">Yelp</a>和 Google 评论上广受赞誉……</blockquote><blockquote>如今，格鲁森坎普·佩雷斯女士是国会中最脆弱的民主党人之一，而迪安公司（以她丈夫的名字命名的家族企业）已成为左派恶意网络攻击的目标。来自全国各地的进步人士正在对建制派进行评论轰炸，他们发帖表达了对这位第一任国会女议员在废除拜登总统学生贷款减免倡议的法案上与共和党站在一起的愤怒。</blockquote><blockquote> “这是我去过的最糟糕的汽车护理中心，”5 月份，在 Gluesenkamp Pérez 女士投票后不久，Yelp 的一位评论员在一篇现在很常见的帖子中写道。 “我的车比我还车时还脏。”他补充道：“玛丽吹嘘她的 PPP 贷款，并在同一句话中说 f 学生，这也无济于事。她太虚伪了。”</blockquote><blockquote>另一位补充道：“这个地方太可怕了。他们收取每日复利的利息。哦等等，那是学生贷款。这个地方确实是最糟糕的。”</blockquote><p>一些突然想对汽车修理发表评论的人似乎很不安，因为他们确信她看起来像个醒悟者。卡尼女士报道：</p><blockquote>她也很年轻，留着钝刘海，经常穿着牛仔裤或阔腿裤套装，看起来更像是进步小队的一员，而不是中间派。与格鲁森坎普·佩雷斯关系密切的人士表示，基于她的外表对她的政治观点的错误假设只会加剧一些左翼人士对她投票记录的愤怒。</blockquote><p>根据人们的外表对人做出肤浅的判断是自由主义法理学的一个标志，但我们许多人对 Yelp 的期望更好。</p><p>进步左派的极端不宽容并不是什么新闻。但引人注目的是，众议员格鲁森坎普·佩雷斯似乎已经表示，她愿意支持代价高昂且误导性的拜登政策——只要该政策与其他代价高昂且误导性的政策相结合。卡尼女士报道：</p><blockquote>早在五月，当格鲁森坎普·佩雷斯 (Gluesenkamp Perez) 投下这一决定性的一票时，她解释了她的理由。她当时表示：“扩大学生债务减免需要与职业和技术教育投资相匹配。”</blockquote><p>听起来像是更多的政府——进步人士就不能找到一种与她合作而不涉及抹黑她家族企业的方法吗？</p><p>也许问题在于，这位议员在阐述立场的过程中，也解释了拜登政策的核心缺陷。 “高等教育的整个前提是你赚更多的钱，”她告诉《泰晤士报》。 “当你拿着刚拿到的研究生学位时去抗议一家机械店，这很讽刺。”</p><p>确实是。正如许多学术研究人员指出的那样，拜登救助计划的受益者必然包括大量富裕的借款人。最近美国银行的消费者检查点报告指出：</p><blockquote>学生贷款持有人将从 9 月份开始恢复还款。我们从数据中看到的一个积极因素是，拥有贷款的人往往收入较高，并且拥有强大的存款缓冲。</blockquote><p>但即使对于那些确实难以负担贷款的人来说，问题是为什么他们所接受的教育的价值并没有达到他们所希望的那么高。去年本专栏<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/biden-bails-out-the-price-gougers-11661460301?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">指出</a>：</p><blockquote>为了转移通货膨胀的话题，拜登总统等政客经常发现指责企业哄抬物价很有用。所谓的哄抬物价通常没有明确的定义。但是，当一个行业经常出售无法产生足够收入来偿还购买资产的债务时，你会怎么称呼它呢？</blockquote><blockquote>当然，拜登让纳税人偿还学生贷款债务的非法计划在许多情况下会给不需要帮助的借款人带来好处。但最大的救助是针对那些获得丰厚报酬的学术工作者，他们提供的产品和服务市场需求很少或根本没有……</blockquote><blockquote>一段时间以来，一直有传言称许多大学学位课程不值高价。如果即使在历史上紧张的劳动力市场中，此类学位的持有者也无法找到资助他们的方法，这意味着学校收费过高。</blockquote><p>到目前为止，还没有人能够有效反驳经济创新集团 Adam Ozimek 的论点：</p><blockquote>如果我们因为学生得到了不好的交易而免除学生债务，那么他们就读的项目应该被禁止提供学生贷款。</blockquote><blockquote>如果他们获得的学位能够收回成本，那么他们就不需要宽恕。如果没有，将来对该计划的访问不应获得补贴。</blockquote><p>也许进步人士更愿意讨论汽车修理。</p><p> ***</p><p><strong>回去工作</strong><br>从某些方面来看，美国人比过去几年更加勤奋。杰弗里·斯帕肖特为《华尔街日报》 <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/americans-working-job-market-prime-age-9fdc339b?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">报道</a>：</p><blockquote>美国劳动力的核心又回来了。</blockquote><blockquote> 25 至 54 岁之间的美国人要么以二十年来未见的速度就业或寻找工作，这一趋势有助于遏制老年婴儿潮一代离开劳动力市场的趋势……壮年工人现在比大流行前的水平多了近 220 万……</blockquote><p> ***</p><p><em>詹姆斯·弗里曼是<a href="https://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1982163984" target="_blank" class="icon none">《成本：特朗普、中国和美国复兴》一书</a>的合著者，也是<a href="https://www.amazon.com/Borrowed-Time-Centuries-Booms-Bailouts/dp/0062669877/ref=asc_df_0062669877/?tag=hyprod-20&amp;linkCode=df0&amp;hvadid=312143020546&amp;hvpos=&amp;hvnetw=g&amp;hvrand=10412016619786864649&amp;hvpone=&amp;hvptwo=&amp;hvqmt=&amp;hvdev=c&amp;hvdvcmdl=&amp;hvlocint=&amp;hvlocphy=9003741&amp;hvtargid=pla-525185269824&amp;psc=1" target="_blank" class="icon none">《借来的时间：花旗两个世纪的繁荣、萧条和救助》一书的合著者。</a></em></p><p> ***</p><p>在<a href="https://twitter.com/FreemanWSJ" target="_blank" class="icon none">Twitter</a>上关注詹姆斯·弗里曼。</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/newsletters?sub=157&amp;mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">订阅最佳网络电子邮件。</a></p><p>如需推荐商品，请发送电子邮件至 best@wsj.com。</p><p> （特蕾莎·沃佐 (Teresa Vozzo) 帮助编译了最佳网络奖。）</p><p> ***</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 24 Jul 2023 22:18:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/new-york-times-reports-on-nasty-progressives-b9a19abd</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/new-york-times-reports-on-nasty-progressives-b9a19abd<author><![CDATA[James Freeman]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>高等教育费用</category><category>教育</category><category>个人财务</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>助学贷款</category><category>大学学院</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>观点</category><category>职业教育</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>高等教育费用</category><category>教育</category><category>个人财务</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>助学贷款</category><category>大学</category><category>大学</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>观点</category><category>职业教育</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Hunter Biden’s Bargain Plea]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>还有人相信乔声称他从未讨论过他儿子的事吗？ <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB11490979256760064080404590108241630472502"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB11490979256760064080404590108241630472502"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="columnist_mini"> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/william-mcgurn"><img width="45" height="45" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/B3-BI560_mcgurn_AM_20180807122138.jpg" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></a></div><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/william-mcgurn" itemprop="url" rel="author">威廉·麦格恩</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 24 日下午 6:13 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/hunter-biden-joe-bargain-plea-tax-irs-whistleblower-archer-ziegler-shapley-burisma-5f891342"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-822862?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">亨特·拜登于 7 月 4 日抵达华盛顿莱斯利·J·麦克奈尔堡。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Ting Shen / Pool/Zuma Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> “逐渐地，然后突然地。”</p><p>这就是欧内斯特·海明威的《太阳照常升起》中的一个人物描述他如何破产的方式，但这很可能是亨特·拜登对他利用家族姓氏进行交易的习惯的解释，而在认罪协议本应永远埋葬这一切的那一刻，他用家族姓氏进行交易的习惯如何在他身上爆炸了。现在，认罪协议本身（定于周三在特拉华州由美国地区法官玛丽莲·诺雷卡批准）已成为一个问题。</p><p>联邦对年轻的拜登先生的税务和金融交易的调查始于 2018 年。笔记本电脑上出现的亨特吸毒和裸体与女性嬉戏的骇人照片不时出现。偶尔也会有人嘲笑乔·拜登涉嫌参与亨特的业务，其中包括一位商业伙伴从未解释的电子邮件，称与一家中国公司达成的交易的 10% 将“由 H 为大人物持有”。</p><p>这是渐进的部分。</p><p>上周突然来了。首先是举报人加里·沙普利和约瑟夫·齐格勒在国会宣誓并公开作证。这些职业国税局调查员提供了有关总统的政治任命人员如何破坏调查的详细信息，向亨特的律师透露有关搜查和采访的信息，禁止询问有关“大人物”的问题，以及如何在涉及布利斯马付款的更严重的税务问题上耗尽诉讼时效。</p><p>然后，就在举报人作证一天后，爱荷华州共和党参议员查克·格拉斯利 (Chuck Grassley) 又投下了一颗重磅炸弹：一份联邦调查局 FD-1023 表格，记录了一位可靠消息来源的说法，即 Burisma 创始人米科拉·兹洛切夫斯基 (Mykola Zlochevsky) 声称，他“被迫”向乔·拜登和亨特·拜登各支付了 500 万美元。新闻媒体尽职尽责地报道说，该表格“未经验证”（大多数关于臭名昭著的斯蒂尔档案的报道都没有这个限定词）。</p><p>但说这些信息未经证实引发了一个关键问题：联邦调查局采取了哪些措施（如果有的话）来核实这些指控？</p><p>想一想。就在两个月前，该局甚至不肯向国会承认 FD-1023 的存在。直到联邦调查局局长克里斯托弗·雷（Christopher Wray）意识到有些人已经看到了一份副本，并且他受到了蔑视的威胁，联邦调查局才承认这一点，并对国会议员进行了有限的审视。</p><p>更令人不安的是，尽管该表格的日期为 2020 年 6 月 30 日，但沙普利和齐格勒表示他们的团队从未见过它。通过发布这份文件，格拉斯利先生向美国人民提供了比司法部和联邦调查局向国税局团队提供的有关贿赂指控的更多详细信息。这台笔记本电脑也是如此，国税局的举报者称他们从未见过这台笔记本电脑。</p><p>除此之外，处理亨特案件的联邦检察官美国检察官戴维·韦斯（David Weiss）也存在可信度问题。司法部长梅里克·加兰（Merrick Garland）明确表示，韦斯先生拥有“完全权力”，可以在任何他想要的地方提出指控，而且从未要求获得特别检察官的地位。但沙普利先生作证（记住，是在宣誓后）韦斯先生告诉他和其他调查人员，他不是“是否提出指控的决定人”。</p><p>韦斯先生本可以澄清这一问题，但他发表了一系列公开声明，但这只会加剧混乱。他曾表示，他拥有“最终权力”，他从未寻求特别顾问地位，如果他提出要求，他就会获得批准。</p><p>这里有人没有说实话。</p><p>传统基金会正在提起诉讼，要求得到答复。它想知道加兰先生说韦斯先生没有要求特别顾问地位时是否撒谎。它希望在周三之前得到答复，届时亨特的请求将获得批准。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>了解更多 大街</h4><p></p><ul class="articleList"><li><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/no-labels-equals-trump-manchin-lieberman-2024-election-biden-rematch-55feda8e?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">“无标签”等于特朗普？</a> <span class="date">2023 年 7 月 17 日</span></li><li><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-ongoing-investigation-dodge-hunter-biden-david-weiss-bribe-question-informant-67c31868?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">针对亨特·拜登的“正在进行的调查”道奇</a><span class="date">2023 年 7 月 10 日</span></li><li><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-man-who-killed-affirmative-action-ed-blum-sffa-harvard-court-race-36143530?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">爱德华·布鲁姆 (Edward Blum)，扼杀平权行动的人</a><span class="date">2023 年 7 月 3 日</span></li></ul></div></div><p>因此，Heritage 要求法院强制司法部公布与韦斯先生和特别顾问问题有关的内部通讯。可能不会赢。但Heritage的说法是正确的，整个亨特·拜登调查的公平性和完整性存在太多问题，不能通过认罪协议将这一切都掩盖起来。</p><p>与此同时，举证责任已经转移。在每次听证会上，国会都会发现令人不安的指控，这些指控越来越具体并得到证人的支持。现在我们了解到，亨特的前最好的朋友和商业伙伴德文·阿彻将向众议院监督委员会通报乔·拜登在担任副总统期间亲自或通过免提参加的客户会议。</p><p>据《纽约邮报》报道，阿彻先生将作证称至少有 24 次此类对话。我们知道的越多，就越难以相信乔·拜登关于他从未与亨特讨论过业务的说法。</p><p>法官很少会撕毁认罪协议。但这完全属于诺雷卡法官的自由裁量权。现在的问题远远超出了亨特·拜登的所作所为，甚至超出了他父亲的参与范围。问题在于处理这次调查并达成这一甜心交易的两个强大机构——联邦调查局和司法部——是否值得信任。</p><p><em>写信至 mcgurn@wsj.com。</em> </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=FDCCF5A6-4DE9-4327-AA4A-056B0B052CB1&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fhunter-biden-joe-bargain-plea-tax-irs-whistleblower-archer-ziegler-shapley-burisma-5f891342&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">杂志社论报道：国税局举报人称司法部干预了他们对亨特·拜登的调查。图片：Zuma Press/AFP/Getty Images 合成：Mark Kelly<span class="imageCredit">华尔街日报互动版</span></p></div></div></section></div></main></div>]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 24 Jul 2023 22:13:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/hunter-biden-joe-bargain-plea-tax-irs-whistleblower-archer-ziegler-shapley-burisma-5f891342</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/hunter-biden-joe-bargain-plea-tax-irs-whistleblower-archer-ziegler-shapley-burisma-5f891342<author><![CDATA[William McGurn]]></author><category>众议院监督委员会</category><category>举报人</category><category>见证</category><category>税</category><category>认罪协议</category><category>辩诉交易</category><category>腐败</category><category>影响力兜售</category><category>间谍机构</category><category>总统</category><category>白色的房子</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>举报人</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>亨特·拜登</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>举报人</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[The Movement Shaping a Modern India]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>主要的印度教民族主义团体表示，宗教和文化将使国家团结起来。 <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB11490979256760064080404590107870847692014"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB11490979256760064080404590107870847692014"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="columnist_mini"> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/walter-russell-mead"><img width="45" height="45" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/B3-BS043_Mead_W_AM_20180912115022.jpg" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></a></div><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/walter-russell-mead" itemprop="url" rel="author">沃尔特·拉塞尔·米德</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 24 日下午 6:12 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-movement-shaping-a-modern-india-rss-modi-hindu-nationalism-e70586d9"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-822552?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> 4 月 16 日，印度钦奈，RSS 人物 Keshav Baliram Hedgewar 和 Madhav Sadashivrao Golwalkar 在一辆汽车上的肖像。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：idrees mohammed/Shutterstock</p></figcaption></figure></div><p><em>印度乌代布尔</em></p><p>当印度基金会邀请我参加一个由印度教民族主义知识分子和与国家人民联盟组织结盟的政治人物参加的周末会议时，我立即接受了。正如我三月份<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/indias-bjp-is-the-worlds-most-important-party-rashtriya-swayamsevak-sangh-narendra-modi-china-ccp-japan-indo-pacific-strategy-hindu-nationalism-496211c2?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">在这些页面中所写的</a>那样，美国人需要更深入地参与一场正在重塑世界上最重要国家之一的政治和文化的运动。</p><p> RSS 是主要的印度教民族主义组织，是现代印度最重要且最具争议的公民社会运动。 Seen as the source of the Hindu nationalist ideology behind the ruling Bharatiya Janata Party, the RSS and the group of affiliated and allied organizations and individuals known as the Sangh Parivar have nurtured a distinctive approach to politics and policy that allowed them to replace the center-left, <a href="https://www.inc.in/our-values/secularism" target="_blank" class="icon none">secularist</a> Indian National Congress as the most powerful force in Indian life.</p><p> Founded in 1925 in Maharashtra by Dr. Keshav Baliram Hedgewar out of a belief that India could take its rightful place in the world only through a movement of national, cultural and religious renewal, the RSS aims to mold the characters of young Indian men (and, since a sister division was founded in 1936, women) through a mix of physical and quasimilitary training, educational summer camps and community-service projects. Selected volunteers become <em>pracharaks</em> , a kind of Hindu version of the Jesuits, living communally, refraining from marriage and working on tasks the leadership assigns.</p><p> In the beginning, the RSS was one of many religious and nationalistic movements emerging out of the ferment of the Indian national awakening of the early 20th century. For many years it remained on the margins of Indian life. Today Hedgewar&#39;s heirs are at the center of power. Prime Minister Narendra Modi joined the RSS at age 8 and became a pracharak in 1972.</p><p> Inevitably, American and Western observers look at Hindu nationalism through the lens of the conflict between Hindus and Muslims that has dominated much of South Asia&#39;s modern history. Whether it is allegations that Mr. Modi, then chief minister of Gujarat, failed to halt the violence that left hundreds of people dead in 2002, or charges that Hindu nationalist authorities turn a blind eye to lynchings and other forms of violence against religious minorities today, the Hindu nationalist movement is widely blamed for exacerbating intercommunal tensions in a country still haunted by the mass murders and violence associated with the 1947 partition of British India. Many Indian and foreign observers see the RSS as cynically stirring the pot of hatred to gain power by appealing to the lowest instincts of voters.</p><p> Concerns about violence are legitimate, but what drives Hindu nationalism is less antagonism against Islam than fear for the future of India. Modern history is a story of multifaith, multilinguistic states falling apart as nationalist forces fight for independence. The Austro-Hungarian and Ottoman empires fell apart. The Soviet Union and Yugoslavia once seemed stable and permanent. Both disappeared almost overnight.</p><p> India is as ethnically and linguistically diverse as Europe or Latin America. As the Indian masses gain access to the internet and social media penetrates villages and slums, what glue can keep India together?</p><p> What unites the subcontinent, say Hindu nationalists, is a shared culture in which Hindu religion plays a central role. Even Indians who aren&#39;t Hindu have been shaped by this traditional culture. Cultivating pride in that heritage and freeing it from injuries of both British and Mughal domination is the only way, Hindu nationalists believe, to hold this vast and diverse population together. Nehruvian secularism and liberal abstractions like “constitutional patriotism” can&#39;t do the job, they argue. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4> Read More Global View</h4><p></p><ul class="articleList"><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinas-economy-hits-the-skids-slow-growth-real-estate-trade-peace-us-unemployment-5b38d155?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">China&#39;s Economy Hits the Skids</a> <span class="date">July 17, 2023</span></li><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/its-too-early-to-count-putin-out-prigozhin-wagner-mutiny-defense-asset-cf7d98e3?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">It&#39;s Too Early to Count Putin Out</a> <span class="date">June 26, 2023</span></li><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-accepts-the-new-indo-pacific-reality-blinken-xi-jinping-defense-spending-a9a9065d?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">China Accepts the New Indo-Pacific Reality</a> <span class="date">June 19, 2023</span></li></ul></div></div><p> Religious leaders in many societies have fought the social and cultural changes that come with modernization and have spearheaded resistance against pro-market policy, education for women and other reforms that successful modernity requires. That&#39;s not what I saw in Udaipur. The RSS leadership knows that India must move and move quickly. A powerful and ambitious China looms to the north. Young people need jobs. Living standards need to rise.</p><p> RSS leaders believe that India can remain united as the shock waves of modernization propagate across the subcontinent only if the changes are seen as grounded in ancient Hindu principles. While conciliating and reassuring more-conservative Hindu thinkers, they are promoting a future-oriented Hinduism in the hope that its ancient religion and culture can bring a united and self-confident India into the 21st century.</p><p>它会起作用吗？ And can a Hindu nationalist India avoid corruption scandals, respect civil liberties and reduce communal tensions and violence? Nobody knows, but these are serious people who care deeply about the future of their country and the world. I left Udaipur more hopeful than when I arrived. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=F5FFC646-850A-4BF7-A92A-47D7AED557FD&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fthe-movement-shaping-a-modern-india-rss-modi-hindu-nationalism-e70586d9&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">期刊编辑报告：Kim Strassel、Bill McGurn 和 Jason Riley 的本周最佳和最差报告。图片：Zuma Press/Invision/AP Composite：Mark Kelly<span class="imageCredit">华尔街日报互动版</span></p></div></div></section></div></main></div>]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 24 Jul 2023 22:12:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-movement-shaping-a-modern-india-rss-modi-hindu-nationalism-e70586d9</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-movement-shaping-a-modern-india-rss-modi-hindu-nationalism-e70586d9<author><![CDATA[Walter Russell Mead]]></author><category> RSS</category><category> hindu nationalism</category><category>印度</category><category>西方</category><category>英国人</category><category>shared heritage</category><category>文化</category><category>社交媒体</category><category>现代化</category><category>Political/General News</category><category>社会/社区</category><category>国际关系</category><category>Politics/International Relations</category><category> Domestic Politics</category><category>宗教</category><category>Content Types</category><category> Commentaries/Opinions</category><category> Factiva Filters</category><category> C&amp;E Executive News Filter</category><category> RSS</category><category> SYND</category><category> WSJ-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>general news</category><category>社会</category><category>community</category><category> international relations</category><category> politics</category><category> domestic politics</category><category> religion</category><category> content types</category><category> commentaries</category><category> opinions</category><category> factiva filters</category><category> c&amp;e executive news filter </category></item><item><title><![CDATA[‘Look’ Review: Life as It Is, Blinkers Removed]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> To pay attention is not solely to concentrate or focus; it can mean entering states of heightened awareness, like a predator on the hunt. <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB11277182998813654381604590096382887103008"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-822898?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Shutterstock / Juriah Mosin </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB11277182998813654381604590096382887103008"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/meghan-cox-gurdon" itemprop="url" rel="author">Meghan Cox Gurdon</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> July 24, 2023 6:11 pm ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/look-review-life-as-it-is-blinkers-removed-794e456"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> As a young man, Christian Madsbjerg was poking around a library and came across a passage by Aristotle that struck him as ridiculous. In “Physics,” Aristotle explained that objects drop earthward because they want to return to the place where they belong. As Mr. Madsbjerg re-read the lines, he felt his derision give way to dizziness. “In [Aristotle&#39;s] world, objects fell to the ground because they were homesick,” Mr. Madsbjerg writes in “Look,” a provocative, sometimes elusive work of inquiry and instruction. That a philosopher two millennia ago knew nothing of gravity was not in itself surprising; what moved Mr. Madsbjerg was the realization that Aristotle must have really believed what he&#39;d written.</p><p> “I have since encountered that vertigo of coalescing insight many, many times,” writes the Danish-born entrepreneur, who has built a career on the pursuit of perceptual breakthroughs. In “Look,” Mr. Madsbjerg attempts to impart the wisdom he has acquired from art and philosophy and from the practical experience of running a corporate consultancy and teaching a class on “human observation” at the New School in New York. His book is full of intriguing goodies: anecdotes and precepts originating in a wide array of sources, as well as summaries of the work of gestalt theorists and practitioners of phenomenology, a discipline he defines as “the study of how the human world works and everything that gives our life meaning.” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
        "><div class="media-object-rich-text"><p> <strong>Look: How to Pay Attention in a Distracted World</strong></p><p> <em>By Christian Madsbjerg</em></p><p> <em>(Riverhead, 234 pages, $29)</em> </p></div></div><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/schemas/9618f397-9a69-46f1-b501-13c5d8046de9.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p> The breadth and vagueness of that definition bespeaks the book&#39;s enthusiastic overreach. There&#39;s a lot here, and a lot of it makes sense, but there are moments when the argument is so diffuse as to feel precarious. At times Mr. Madsbjerg teeters on the edge of banality, even incoherence. Yet he never tips over, for there is unmistakably truth in what he&#39;s getting at. And, to be fair, the distinction between apparent understanding and deep understanding is difficult to draw. It is difficult even to describe. Mr. Madsbjerg does a heroic job of seeking to capture the experience of sudden insight.</p><p> The “richest reality,” he argues, is reached not by thinking but by looking—by which he means broadly using one&#39;s perceptual apparatus. This dictum sounds simple to follow, but it is not. Looking takes time. Looking requires silencing the chattering mind. Looking means not only letting the eye follow the shiny bouncing object but also taking in the vast realm of context around the object and noticing what is not shiny and not bouncing. Perhaps most challengingly, it means surrendering the idea that we are necessarily seeing what we think we see. For, as Mr. Madsbjerg explains, “perception happens inside us; we change what we see to reflect who and where we are in the world.”</p><p> A rose may be a rose may be a rose, to mangle Gertrude Stein, but a rose is going to have very different meanings for a botanist, an interior designer or a love-struck suitor. When we glance at a rose—or any other thing—we see it amid the connotations it holds for us. This is the idea of gestalt, the recognizable “wholeness” of things. To take another example, few of us would stop to assess the color, size, shape and composition of a dining table and a set of chairs before drawing conclusions about their nature and purpose. The same is true with the gestalt of a picnic lunch or a museum gallery or a crowded bus stop: It&#39;s easy to register a scene without noticing any of the details.</p><p> This capacity to make rapid sense of what we see equips us to get on with daily life, but it can also be an obstacle to clarity, fitting us with blinkers and causing us to miss important signals. “Look” is full of stories of people who have struggled to see the forest for the trees, or the trees for the forest, or the reason the forest is growing where it is and not some other place. One anecdote tells of an executive at an electronics company who was so intent on developing sophisticated big-screen televisions that he missed the cultural shift toward TV-viewing on laptops and smartphones. Another relates how the city-born biographer Robert Caro had to spend long hours in the open-skied isolation of rural Texas before he felt he could begin to understand his subject, Lyndon Johnson.</p><p> Looking through an ideological lens can also be blinding, as Mr. Madsbjerg knows firsthand, having grown up in a Marxist milieu on a Danish island in the Baltic Sea. “For a teenager, Communism was a totalizing, energetic, and angry faith,” he writes. “I was enraptured by fervor—furious about the class inequities in the world.” Only when his revolutionary ardor faded was he able to see how the ideology had distorted his perception of the world. The fall of the Berlin Wall became, in his telling, the impetus to begin a quest to understand how fashions in thinking advance and retreat; why people change their minds; and whether it is possible to anticipate social change, to “feel signs of a storm approaching.”</p><p> How, then, to proceed for the reader who wants to “pay attention in a distracted world”? The first step, it seems, is to understand that attentiveness can take many forms. To pay attention is not solely, as we might think, to focus or concentrate; it can mean entering other states of heightened awareness, such as the multi-dimensional vigilance of a predator on the hunt or the “glaze of attention”—the generalized alertness, or supple readiness, of, say, an athlete on the playing field or a driver in fast-moving traffic.</p><p> With our senses alive and in a condition of receptivity, we may find it easier to notice the trend, the anomaly or the eloquent social silence that augurs a coming shift. Such skills are useful at work, of course, but also at home. “The future is never a theoretical prospect for any of us. You can observe it in your everyday reality,” Mr. Madsbjerg promises. “The most challenging thing for all of us to see is what is really there.”</p><p> <em>Mrs. Gurdon, a Journal contributor, is the author of “The Enchanted Hour: The Miraculous Power of Reading Aloud in the Age of Distraction.”</em></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 24 Jul 2023 22:11:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/look-review-life-as-it-is-blinkers-removed-794e456</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/look-review-life-as-it-is-blinkers-removed-794e456<author><![CDATA[Meghan Cox Gurdon]]></author><category>图书</category><category>Political/General News</category><category> Arts/Entertainment</category><category> Content Types</category><category> Factiva Filters</category><category> C&amp;E Exclusion Filter</category><category>评论</category><category>SYND</category><category> WSJ-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>观点</category><category>图书</category><category>政治的</category><category>general news</category><category> arts</category><category>娱乐</category><category>content types</category><category> factiva filters</category><category> c&amp;e exclusion filter</category><category> reviews</category><category>观点</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Spain’s High-Stakes Election Stalemate]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> A left-wing coalition with separatists could imperil the country. <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB11786258192805913745104590108391422761452"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB11786258192805913745104590108391422761452"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name">Tunku Varadarajan</span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> July 24, 2023 6:10 pm ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/spain-high-stakes-political-stalemate-election-sanchez-vox-feijoo-right-catalan-955ad1f3"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-822866?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Spanish Prime Minister Pedro Sánchez addresses supporters in Madrid, July 23.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Cesar Luis De Luca/Zuma Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Foreign politics can be as confounding as other people&#39;s marriages. So a version of the question “What does she see in him?” is an apt one to ask Spain after it failed in Sunday&#39;s elections to kick Pedro Sánchez out of office.</p><p> Mr. Sánchez has been prime minister since 2018, when he stitched together a ruling coalition of his own Socialist Party with Communists and regional separatists. After five years of misrule—including granting every Spaniard over 16 the right to assign his own gender—he was expected to lose power to the conservative Popular Party. The PP is headed by Alberto Núñez Feijóo, a man who, while achingly dull, is a moral paragon compared with Mr. Sánchez.</p><p> Yet the Socialists finished in a jaunty second place, better positioned to form a coalition government than Mr. Feijóo, who won a plurality of seats in Parliament but is unlikely to win over enough of the other parties to his side. Polls predicted a win for him, but the PP fell far short of the numbers it needs to form a government in coalition with its partner Vox, a more robustly conservative party than the center-right PP. The expression Spain&#39;s media and leftists use to smear Vox is <em>extrema derecha</em> —far right—deployed reflexively to gin up frightening echoes of erstwhile dictator Francisco Franco (1892-1975) and his Catholic-flavored fascism. (The media seldom described the communists in Mr. Sánchez&#39;s last government as “extreme left.”)</p><p> Conservative Americans will find this demonization of Vox vexing. The party&#39;s leader differs from Ron DeSantis in his politics only in his degree of support for Ukraine. (Mr. DeSantis is less wholehearted.) But on social policy, culture wars and migration, the two men are kindred spirits. Vox has been so successfully slandered as beyond the pale that the Socialists energized their base to vote once more for a discredited Mr. Sánchez. This would, they said, avert the return to government of Francoists in the guise of Vox, in partnership with the PP. And no other party will govern with the PP if Vox is also in a coalition.</p><p> Since the math of the results doesn&#39;t allow the PP to govern without Vox, the second-placed Socialists will be asked if they can form a government after Mr. Feijóo tries and fails. It is likely they can, and therein lies national peril.</p><p> Mr. Sánchez will need the backing of Catalan separatists, who are hell-bent on breaking up Spain. Carles Puigdemont, the most rabid of this tribe, could tip Mr. Sánchez over the line and into power. Mr. Puigdemont is in exile in Belgium after masterminding an unlawful Catalan independence referendum in 2017. He has named his price for parliamentary support: an amnesty for separatists; and another referendum for Catalan “self-determination.”</p><p> If Mr. Sánchez bites, he&#39;ll win power for himself, but at the cost, potentially, of the survival of Spain as we know it. It is too soon to say what he will do. But we&#39;d do well to remember that he&#39;s a politician with few scruples—if any.</p><p> <em>Mr. Varadarajan, a Journal contributor, is a fellow at the American Enterprise Institute and at NYU Law School&#39;s Classical Liberal Institute.</em> </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=F5FFC646-850A-4BF7-A92A-47D7AED557FD&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fspain-high-stakes-political-stalemate-election-sanchez-vox-feijoo-right-catalan-955ad1f3&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">期刊编辑报告：Kim Strassel、Bill McGurn 和 Jason Riley 的本周最佳和最差报告。图片：Zuma Press/Invision/AP Composite：Mark Kelly<span class="imageCredit">华尔街日报互动版</span></p></div></div></section></div></main></div>]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 24 Jul 2023 22:10:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/spain-high-stakes-political-stalemate-election-sanchez-vox-feijoo-right-catalan-955ad1f3</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/spain-high-stakes-political-stalemate-election-sanchez-vox-feijoo-right-catalan-955ad1f3<category>西班牙</category><category>选举</category><category>声音</category><category>coalition</category><category>正确的</category><category>独立</category><category>catalan</category><category> Political/General News</category><category> Politics/International Relations</category><category> Domestic Politics</category><category> Content Types</category><category> Commentaries/Opinions</category><category> Factiva Filters</category><category> C&amp;E Executive News Filter</category><category> SYND</category><category> WSJ-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>观点</category><category>政治的</category><category>general news</category><category> politics</category><category> international relations</category><category> domestic politics</category><category> content types</category><category> commentaries</category><category> opinions</category><category> factiva filters</category><category> c&amp;e executive news filter</category><category>观点</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[We Audit the Auditors, and We Found Trouble]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> PCAOB inspectors are turning up an increasing number of deficiencies. That&#39;s bad for investors. <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB12136984570395233300204590102422672461614"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB12136984570395233300204590102422672461614"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name">Erica Y. Williams</span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> July 24, 2023 6:09 pm ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/we-audit-the-auditors-and-we-found-trouble-accountability-capital-markets-c5587f05"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-822573?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> George W. Bush signs a bill at the White House, July 30, 2002.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: kevin lamarque/Reuters</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> High-quality audits are essential to the integrity of US capital markets and the protection of investors. As President George W. Bush said when signing the law creating the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board to oversee audits of public companies: “The fundamentals of a free market—buying and selling, saving and investing—require clear rules and confidence in basic fairness. The only risks—the only fair risks—are based on honest information.”</p><p> It is therefore unacceptable that audit quality is trending down for the second year in a row. A PCAOB report <a href="https://assets.pcaobus.org/pcaob-dev/docs/default-source/documents/staff-preview-2022-inspection-observations-spotlight.pdf?sfvrsn=63b51390_2" target="_blank" class="icon none">released Monday</a> finds that when inspection reports are finalized later this year, PCAOB inspectors expect that approximately 40% of the audits they reviewed in 2022 will have had one or more deficiencies, in which the audit firm failed to obtain sufficient appropriate evidence to support its opinion. That is up 6 percentage points from 2021, which was 5 points higher than the deficiency rate in 2020.</p><p> This means audit opinions were signed without completing the audit work required to verify the financial statements. That is a serious problem at any rate, and 40% is completely unacceptable.</p><p> The PCAOB hasn&#39;t hesitated to bring enforcement cases against auditors when appropriate. Last year we doubled the number of enforcement orders compared with 2021 and imposed the highest total penalties in history.</p><p> At the same time, we will continue conducting inspections to hold audit firms accountable.</p><p> Transparency is one of the most powerful tools the PCAOB has to improve audit quality. Sharing our inspection results empowers audit committees and boards of directors—which are responsible for hiring auditors of public companies—to hold audit firms accountable directly.</p><p> As part of its efforts to improve transparency, <a href="https://pcaobus.org/news-events/news-releases/news-release-detail/pcaob-enhances-transparency-of-inspection-reports-with-new-section-on-auditor-independence-and-more" target="_blank" class="icon none">earlier this year</a> the PCAOB began including more information in our public inspection reports than ever before, including information about auditor independence violations. Last week we added more tools on our website to make it easier to compare deficiency rates across audit firms.</p><p> We hope boards of directors and audit committees will use PCAOB inspection reports to hold audit firms accountable for high-quality results and ask tough questions on behalf of their investors.</p><p> Audit committees should know the deficiency rate of the audit firm they hire and how it compares with other options. They should ask audit firms if the audits of their company have been inspected and, if so, for the results. They should find out whether the specific auditors who are assigned to work with their company have had their audits for other clients inspected and what the results were.</p><p> Similarly, investors should engage with investor relations and the audit committees of the companies in which they invest and encourage them to seek out audit firms with quality records.</p><p> Ultimately, the responsibility falls on auditors to correct the problems that led to deficiencies in their audits. But accountability from their clients offers a powerful incentive to find solutions. The root causes of increased deficiencies vary from firm to firm, and there is no one-size-fits-all explanation for deteriorating audit quality.</p><p> Some firms point to the continuing effects of Covid-19, including the great resignation and heightened competition for talent. Three years after the pandemic began, these challenges are no longer new and firms should have a strategy to meet them.</p><p> At the same time, Covid-19 can&#39;t simply explain away a 40% deficiency rate. Many of the deficiencies PCAOB inspectors identified have recurred for years, well before the pandemic.</p><p> Now is the time for solutions, not excuses.</p><p> Investors trust audits to verify the financial reporting that underpins our capital markets. Auditors must deliver quality results worthy of that trust.</p><p> <em>Ms. Williams is chairman of the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board.</em> </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
